| Feature                | `driver.get()`                          | `driver.navigate().to()`                     |
| ---------------------- | --------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| **Purpose**            | URL open karta hai                      | URL open karta hai                           |
| **Wait Behavior**      | Page fully load hone tak wait karta hai | Page load hone ka strict wait nahi karta     |
| **Navigation Methods** | Sirf URL open kar sakta hai             | Back, Forward, Refresh bhi support karta hai |
| **Usage**              | Simple page opening                     | Navigation operations                        |

---------------------------------
driver.get() is used to open a URL and waits until the page is fully loaded, whereas driver.navigate().to() is 
also used to open a URL but it belongs to 
the navigation interface which supports additional operations like back, forward, and refresh.
